          Field Representative (FR)  Flexible hours! Interesting work! Help your community!  If you enjoy meeting people, the U.S. Census Bureau has a few openings for Part-Time Field Representatives. The Census Bureau conducts a variety of censuses and surveys. Every month, quarter, and year we  conduct surveys  with households and businesses. Field Representatives are selected based on openings in the county or city in which they live.  Bilingual applicants are encouraged to apply. Jobs may not be available in all areas.   This is an ideal job for an organized,self-starter who enjoys meeting and talking with people. Successful candidates will be persistent, persuasive and professional with a pleasant and courteous demeanor.  Pay and reimbursements:  The pay rate is $14.30 per hour. You will also be reimbursed for authorized expenses, including$0.58 cents per mile.  Requirements:   Be at least 18 years old  U.S. Citizenship  Valid driver's license, vehicle access  Be available to work days, evenings, and weekends   How to apply:  Call 1-800-992-3529formore information on how to apply.    Bilingual applicants are encouraged to apply.   Full Recruiting Bulletin 19-3200-001 available at:  Field Representative GG-0303-03/04 Duties and Qualifications Recruiting Bulletin No. 19-3200-001 available at: https://www.census.gov/fieldjobs      THIS AGENCY PROVIDES REASONABLE ACCOMMODATIONS TO APPLICANTS WITH DISABILITES. IF YOU NEED A REASONABLE ACCOMMODATION FOR ANY PART OF THE APPLICATION AND HIRING PROCESS, PLEASE NOTIFY THE AGENCY at 1-800-992-3529. THE DECISION OF GRANTING A REASONABLE ACCOMMODATION WILL BE A CASE-BY-CASE BASIS.        THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF COMMERCE IS AN        EQUAL EMPLOYMENT OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER          All qualified applicants will be considered regardless of age, race, color, sex, creed, national origin, lawful political affiliation, disability, marital status, affiliation with an employee organization, sexual orientation, or other non-merit facto